Product description

Flavor:Regular  |  Size:12 Count (Pack of 6)

Before coffee was complicated, great coffee was simply fresh, bold, and flavorful. This classic donut companion contains the highest quality Arabica beans... dunking is encouraged. Some people won’t admit it, but the best part of a donut is the coffee that goes with it. Without coffee, donuts are just another confection. But donut shop coffee? That’s a different story. The Original Donut Shop Coffee lingers on your tongue and warms the soul. It brightens your day like a big scoop of sprinkles. And who doesn’t like sprinkles? If you go through life as if it’s a sweet surprise filled with jelly and covered in frosting, The Original Donut Shop Coffee is for you.

Matthew
1.0 out of 5 starsDefective, Fraudulent or Poor Quality Control
March 14, 2017
Flavor: RegularSize: 12 Count (Pack of 6)Verified Purchase
UPDATE: I reviewed this coffee previously and gave it 5/5. I had a recent purchase that was less than stellar. I believe that I purchased some defective or fraudulent cups. These cups are labeled "THIS UNIT NOT LABELED FOR RETAIL SALE". I have previously enjoyed this coffee, so I purchased a large quantity of the K-Cups expecting the quality that I have had in the past. I thought I was having trouble with my brewer as I was getting errors on the screen saying that it was under high pressure! I perform routine maintenance on my coffee maker. Additionally, 3/4 or more of the K-Cups would spill copious amounts of coffee grounds into my coffee cups. The 1/4 that do not pour all of the grounds into my cup taste weak and stale. So, since my purchase, I brew around 3-4 cups of coffee daily to achieve a less than desirable cup of coffee... I contacted Keurig and performed maintenance on my machine. I was instructed to return my machine and was appalled when my new machine was doing the same thing! I purchased some different coffee from my local grocery store rather than using my Donut Shop K-Cups from Amazon and have not had a problem since. All this headache and it was the K-Cups after all!!! So, I simply cannot recommend this coffee any longer and do not know if I would waste the money and purchase more as I do not know if it was fraudulent or simply poor quality control on the Donut Shop's part.
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
Previous Review: I can see why this is so popular. The Original Donut Shop K-cup is just a good all-around cup of coffee. This K-cup isn’t a flavored coffee. For my daily coffee, I want a coffee that smells great, is not overly “burnt” tasting and doesn’t leave a sour aftertaste. This isn’t gourmet coffee, but it is a basic medium bodied coffee that tastes almost like a light-roast breakfast blend. The Donut Shop coffee is fairly smooth and not too acidic, but does have a slight aftertaste. This coffee is best alongside breakfast. I would compare it to Green Mountain Breakfast Blend, but say this one is a little better in my opinion. For these reasons, this is my daily go to coffee.

Marcos Della
4.0 out of 5 starsSame good ole Donut Shop quality... little hefty on the price...
January 31, 2018
Flavor: RegularSize: 12 Count (Pack of 6)Verified Purchase
Loved these things however once it was all said and done and we did the math, even with the "free" prime shipping, these ended up costing significantly more than going to the local Costco and purchasing the K-cups there. I love the brand and of course its hard to go wrong with K-cups in general (although I do have one comment on that below) but the price unfortunately just sort of lost it for me.

One thing on the K-cups I did notice is that unlike several other brands of coffee, this particular K-cup from this shipment is back pressuring my Keruig more than others. That is, it takes almost twice as long to push the water through the K-cup than other brands of coffee and sometimes it takes so long that the Keruig stops and I get only 2/3s a cup of coffee. Note that this Keruig has been descaled and cleaned with actual regular maintenance on the troublesome one-way valve as well as the rotating pump. No deep analysis as to why this is other than (short of cutting open a couple cups and comparing them) it seems like the coffee might be denser in the filter part of the K-cup (for those that don't know, some K-cups are more expensive because they put extra filters in the space and encapsulate the coffee in there. Things like hot chocolate use no filters and just flush the contents into your cup).

5.0 out of 5 stars... is a review of the Keurig Hot Donut Shop Sweet and Creamy Regular Coffee K Cups
October 15, 2017
Flavor: Sweet & Creamy RegularSize: 60 CountVerified Purchase
This is a review of the Keurig Hot Donut Shop Sweet and Creamy Regular Coffee K Cups.

Summary – I would compare this to a cup of coffee which has two creamers and two sugar packets and could not be happier. It is like an all in one deal and no need to run to fridge or cabinet to finalize my morning coffee. My best coffee of choice so far and would recommend to anyone who likes the cup of coffee as above.

I did note when I remove the used pod, they have a much larger hole in the top and sometimes leave a drip or two after use. Guessing this may be caused by the extra pressure in the pod itself from the added ingredients?

If you are on the fence, I would recommend you give them a shot. Amazing in flavor. Rich, creamy, sweet and goes down smooth!
